THE family of a 38-year-old woman who was found dead in a sugarcane field on Wednesday is leaving everything in the hands of the police.Nozipho Sishi from Lambothi Village, Inyoni, near Mandeni was found dead at a nearby sugarcane farm.Police believe she was strangled.Her aunt, Gloria Sibiya (60), told Daily Sun the family is hopeful the police will catch the person who killed her.She said Nozipho left home last Saturday to go to church but never returned. &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t know what happened to her but her church members say they saw her near the freeway after church. She told them she was going to meet her mother, who had gone to another church service,&rdquo; Gloria said.&ldquo;But her mother was not aware of the meeting.&rdquo; KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said police at Inyoni cop shop received a call about a woman&rsquo;s body in a sugarcane field. &ldquo;The members went to the farm where they found the body of a woman, which had strangle marks on it,&rdquo; said Mbhele. &ldquo;The motive for her killing is unknown. &ldquo;A case of murder was opened for investigation. &ldquo;We are appealing to anyone who might have information to contact their local police station or to call Crime Stop on 08600 10111,&rdquo; Mbhele said.